---
description: Guidance for editing research, product, and architecture docs
globs: "docs/**/*.md,README.md,deep-research-report-*.md"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Keep planning documents crisp and decision-oriented.
- Preserve the distinction between product docs, architecture docs, source strategy docs, and execution plans.
- Link to the canonical file instead of repeating the same decision in multiple places.
- If a document changes repo structure or workflow expectations, update `docs/REPO_STRUCTURE_PLAN.md` or `docs/README.md`.
